## Features

- **Manual Mode** — Use WASD to navigate the maze
- **Auto Solver** — Stack-based DFS algorithm finds the exit automatically
- **Undo** — Stack-powered unlimited undo (press U)
- **Random Mazes** — Every maze is randomly generated using stack-based DFS
- **Live Stack View** — Watch the stack change in real time
- **Step Counter** — Tracks your moves

## Stack Applications in This Project

| Application | Description |
|-------------|-------------|
| DFS Maze Generation | Stack replaces recursion for random wall carving |
| DFS Maze Solving | Stack stores the search path, pops on dead ends |
| Undo Operation | Each move is pushed; undo pops to restore state |
| Path Backtracking | Dead end → pop from stack → try another direction |

## Quick Start

### Prerequisites

- Java JDK 8 or higher
- A terminal that supports ANSI colors (Linux/macOS Terminal, Windows Terminal, Git Bash)

### Step 1 — Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/stack-maze-explorer.git
cd stack-maze-explorer
```

### Step 2 — Compile

```bash
javac -d out src/*.java
```

This creates compiled `.class` files in the `out/` directory.

### Step 3 — Run

```bash
java -cp out MazeGame
```

You should see the welcome screen. Press **Enter** to start.

### Step 4 — Play

```
W / ↑  — Move up
S / ↓  — Move down
A / ←  — Move left
D / →  — Move right
U      — Undo last move (stack pop!)
R      — Generate a new random maze
P      — Auto-solve with DFS (watch the stack work)
Q      — Quit
```

### Step 5 — Take Screenshots for README

**On macOS:**
```bash
# Full screen
Cmd + Shift + 3

# Selected area
Cmd + Shift + 4
```

**On Windows:**
```bash
# Snipping Tool
Win + Shift + S
```

**On Linux:**
```bash
# Using gnome-screenshot
gnome-screenshot -a
```

Then save screenshots to the `screenshots/` folder:

```bash
mkdir -p screenshots
# Move your screenshots into this folder, for example:
mv ~/Desktop/Screenshot*.png screenshots/
```

### Step 6 — Add Screenshots to README

Open this `README.md` and uncomment the image lines at the top, updating filenames:

```markdown
![Main Menu](screenshots/main_menu.png)
![Gameplay](screenshots/gameplay.png)
![Auto Solve](screenshots/auto_solve.png)
![Victory](screenshots/victory.png)
```

## Project Structure

```
stack-maze-explorer/
├── src/
│   ├── MazeGame.java          # Main entry + game loop
│   ├── GameStack.java         # Custom stack implementation
│   ├── MazeGenerator.java     # Maze generator (DFS + stack)
│   ├── MazeSolver.java        # Maze solver (DFS + stack)
│   ├── Position.java          # Grid position class
│   └── MazeRenderer.java      # Console renderer with ANSI colors
├── screenshots/                # Your game screenshots go here
│   ├── main_menu.png
│   ├── gameplay.png
│   ├── auto_solve.png
│   └── victory.png
├── README.md
├── .gitignore
└── LICENSE
```

## Core Algorithm — Stack-Based DFS Maze Solving

```
1. Push start position onto stack
2. Loop until stack is empty or exit is found:
   a. Peek at stack top (current position)
   b. If it's the exit → success! Stack contents = solution path
   c. If there's an unvisited neighbor → push it onto stack
   d. If no unvisited neighbors → pop (backtrack)
3. Empty stack = no solution exists
```

